   <titleInfo>
      <title>Letter, Southgate Cregmile in Nashville, Tenn. to Mother, 1862, July 14</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>1862 July 14 Southgate Cregmile in Nashville, Tenn. to his Mother (Eleanor Griffin). Assures her that everyone there is well. Camping in town, where both the thirty day guard duty and the place they are staying pleases him. Purged an abandoned house of its contents producing a wagon load of hidden army uniforms, guns, even several bolts of muslin cloth. Provost guard on high alert because of a three thousand member enemy cavalry camped only three miles up river.</abstract>
